    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"887557\">@Noah Anderson</span> You can just work with <code>Type u</code> directly. Your current <code>Sets</code> has objects of the form <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>str</mtext><mo>⊆</mo><mtext>carrier</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\text{str} \\subseteq \\text{carrier}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7719em;vertical-align:-0.136em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">str</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">⊆</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6679em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">carrier</span></span></span></span></span>, but then you ignore the carrier when defining homs.</p>",
        "id": 508211859,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1742978919
    },
    {
